  "prompt": "What do you do when you have no friends?",
  "response": "If you're feeling lonely and have no friends, here are some suggestions:\n\n1. Join social groups or clubs related to your interests\n- Meetup groups\n- Sports teams\n- Book clubs\n- Hobby groups\n\n2. Take classes or workshops\n- Learn a new skill\n- Meet people with similar interests\n\n3. Use social apps and websites\n- Friendship apps like Bumble BFF\n- Social media groups\n- Online communities\n\n4. Volunteer\n- Meet people while helping others\n- Develop social connections\n- Feel more engaged in your community\n\n5. Practice social skills\n- Work on communication\n- Be open and approachable\n- Show genuine interest in others\n\n6. Engage in social activities\n- Attend local events\n- Go to community gatherings\n- Visit local cafes or social spaces\n\n7. Consider professional help\n- Talk to a therapist\n- Get guidance on building social connections\n- Address potential underlying issues\n\n8. Be patient and kind to yourself\n- Building friendships takes time\n- Focus on personal growth\n- Stay positive\n\n9. Participate in workplace or school social activities\n- Team-building events\n- Group projects\n- After-work/school gatherings\n\nRemember that quality matters more than quantity when it comes to friendships.",
